This paper is about training conversational agents using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves training neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves modeling the interaction as a stochastic collaborative game, which falls under the category of robotics and control, making cs.SD (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
